quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  25,45,Have you not seen how your Lord spreads the shadow? Had He willed He could have made it still - We make the sun its guide
  25,46,Then We contract it towards Us with a gradual contraction in easy stages
  25,47,"And He it is who made the night a covering for you; and sleep for repose, and made the day a resurrection"
  25,48,And He it is who sent the winds as glad tidings heralding His mercy; and We send down purifying water from the sky
  25,49,"That We may quicken therewith the dead land, and slake the thirst of the things We have created - beasts and men in great numbers"
  25,50,"And verily, We have repeated it (the lesson) in various ways among them that they may remember; but most of mankind begrudge aught save ingratitude"
  25,51,"But, had We pleased, We could have raised a Warner in every village (or population centre)"
  25,52,"So obey not the disbelievers, but strive against them herewith (with the Quran) with great endeavour"
  25,53,"He it is who has set free the two bodies of water (rivers and seas), one palatable and sweet, and the other salty and bitter, and has set a barrier between them, forbidding passage"
  25,54,"And He it is who has created man from water, and has appointed for him kindred by blood and kindred by marriage for your Lord is ever Powerful"
  25,55,Yet they worship beside Allah what can neither profit them nor harm them; but the disbeliever is ever a partisan of evil against his Lord
  25,56,We have only sent you to give glad tidings and as a Warner
  25,57,"Say, \"I ask you for no reward for this, save that whoever will may choose a way unto his Lord"
  25,58,And rely you upon the Living One who dies not; and celebrate His praise; He is sufficient as Knower about the faults of His servants
  25,59,"He who created the heavens and the earth, and what is between them, in six days, and then mounted the Throne; the Beneficent! Ask any one who is aware concerning Him"
  25,60,"And when it is said unto them, \"Adore you the Beneficent\", they say, \"What is the Beneficent? Shall we adore what you do order us?\" And it only increases their aversion"